flowRoot.flowPara: The home location is included when Clocks is run for the first time
Home is set to the system timezone/location when the user was first set up (ie. not the current physical location or the current system location)
The home location always occupies position one in the grid
Current location is displayed when the physical location differs from the home location
If a grid tile is added for the current location, it is placed at position two

text.tspan: Click on items to select them
Click on items to select them

flowRoot.flowPara: Selection mode allows you to set a location as home
If the current location is "dynamic only" (ie. only present because of geolocation) it cannot be deleted
The home location can be deleted
You can also unset the home location using the "Set as Home Timezone" toggle
If the current location is "dynamic only" (ie. only present because of geolocation) it cannot be deleted
Current locations that have not been manually added should be removed from the grid after you have left them
